<p>Herbert Hoover, the 31st president of the United States, was born on 8/10/1874, in West Branch, Iowa. He was 54 when he took office on 3/4/1929. Member: Republican Party.

	
		He left office on 3/4/1933.
	

	His occupation before the presidency: Engineer.
	His college: Stanford.

	
		He died in New York, New York, on 10/20/1964.
	
</p>

